Note:
Runa Standard Library: Configuration Loader Module

Provides comprehensive configuration file loading capabilities supporting multiple formats
(JSON, YAML, TOML, INI, XML, ENV), hierarchical configuration merging, file watching,
and robust error handling. This module serves as the foundation for application
configuration management with production-ready features.

Features:
- Multi-format configuration file loading (JSON, YAML, TOML, INI, XML, ENV)
- Hierarchical configuration merging with precedence rules
- Configuration file watching and hot-reloading
- Schema validation and type conversion
- Environment variable interpolation in config files
- Configuration templating and preprocessing
- Remote configuration loading (HTTP/HTTPS, S3, etc.)
- Configuration caching and performance optimization
- Detailed error reporting and debugging
- Configuration versioning and migration support

Supported Formats:
- JSON: JavaScript Object Notation with comments support
- YAML: YAML Ain't Markup Language with anchors and references
- TOML: Tom's Obvious, Minimal Language
- INI: Traditional INI files with sections
- XML: Extensible Markup Language with XPath support
- ENV: Environment variable files (.env format)
- Properties: Java-style properties files

Security Features:
- Secure file access with permission validation
- Configuration encryption and decryption
- Sensitive value detection and masking
- Configuration integrity verification

Thread Safety: All loading operations are thread-safe and support
concurrent access across multiple execution contexts.
:End Note

Import "stdlib/config/environment" as environment
Import "stdlib/io/file" as file
Import "stdlib/json/json" as json

Note: Core Configuration Loader Types
Type ConfigFormat is:
    | JSON
    | YAML  
    | TOML
    | INI
    | XML
    | ENV
    | PROPERTIES
    | AUTO

Type ConfigFile is Dictionary with:
    path as String
    format as ConfigFormat
    exists as Boolean defaults to false
    readable as Boolean defaults to false
    size as Integer defaults to 0
    last_modified as Float defaults to 0.0
    encoding as String defaults to "utf-8"
    permissions as String defaults to ""
    content_hash as Optional[String] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type LoaderOptions is Dictionary with:
    strict_mode as Boolean defaults to false
    allow_missing_files as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_interpolation as Boolean defaults to true
    interpolation_syntax as String defaults to "shell"
    enable_includes as Boolean defaults to false
    max_include_depth as Integer defaults to 10
    enable_caching as Boolean defaults to true
    cache_ttl as Float defaults to 300.0
    enable_validation as Boolean defaults to false
    validation_schema as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to None
    encoding as String defaults to "utf-8"
    file_size_limit as Integer defaults to 10485760
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type LoadResult[T] is:
    | LoadSuccess with data as T and source_file as String and format as ConfigFormat and load_time as Float
    | LoadError with error_message as String and error_code as String and source_file as String
    | LoadPartial with data as T and errors as List[String] and source_file as String

Type MergeStrategy is:
    | OVERRIDE
    | MERGE_DEEP
    | MERGE_SHALLOW
    | APPEND_LISTS
    | UNION_MAPS

Type ConfigCache is Dictionary with:
    cached_configs as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to dictionary containing
    cache_timestamps as Dictionary[String, Float] defaults to dictionary containing
    cache_hashes as Dictionary[String, String] defaults to dictionary containing
    cache_hits as Integer defaults to 0
    cache_misses as Integer defaults to 0
    max_cache_size as Integer defaults to 100
    ttl_seconds as Float defaults to 300.0
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
:End Note

Note: Core Configuration Loading Functions
Process called "load_configuration_file" that takes path as String and format as Optional[ConfigFormat] and options as Optional[LoaderOptions] returns LoadResult[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_options be options if options is not None else create_default_loader_options
    Let final_format be format if format is not None else detect_config_format with path as path
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate file access
        Let file_validation be validate_config_file_access with:
            path as path
            options as final_options
        
        If not file_validation.accessible:
            Return LoadError with:
                error_message as "Cannot access configuration file: " plus file_validation.error_message
                error_code as "FILE_ACCESS_ERROR"
                source_file as path
        
        Note: Check cache if enabled
        If final_options.enable_caching:
            Let cache_result be check_configuration_cache with:
                path as path
                file_info as file_validation.file_info
            
            If cache_result.found and not cache_result.expired:
                Return LoadSuccess with:
                    data as cache_result.data
                    source_file as path
                    format as final_format
                    load_time as get_current_timestamp minus start_time
        
        Note: Read file content
        Let content_result be read_config_file_content with:
            path as path
            encoding as final_options.encoding
            size_limit as final_options.file_size_limit
        
        If not content_result.success:
            Return LoadError with:
                error_message as "Failed to read configuration file: " plus content_result.error_message
                error_code as "FILE_READ_ERROR"
                source_file as path
        
        Let file_content be content_result.content
        
        Note: Apply preprocessing if enabled
        If final_options.enable_interpolation:
            Let interpolated_content be interpolate_configuration_content with:
                content as file_content
                syntax as final_options.interpolation_syntax
                options as final_options
            
            If interpolated_content.success:
                Set file_content to interpolated_content.result
            Else If final_options.strict_mode:
                Return LoadError with:
                    error_message as "Configuration interpolation failed: " plus interpolated_content.error_message
                    error_code as "INTERPOLATION_ERROR"
                    source_file as path
        
        Note: Parse configuration based on format
        Let parse_result be parse_configuration_content with:
            content as file_content
            format as final_format
            options as final_options
        
        Match parse_result:
            When ParseSuccess:
                Let loaded_data be parse_result.data
                
                Note: Handle includes if enabled
                If final_options.enable_includes:
                    Let include_result be process_configuration_includes with:
                        data as loaded_data
                        base_path as get_directory_from_path with path as path
                        options as final_options
                        depth as 0
                    
                    If include_result.success:
                        Set loaded_data to include_result.merged_data
                    Else If final_options.strict_mode:
                        Return LoadError with:
                            error_message as "Include processing failed: " plus include_result.error_message
                            error_code as "INCLUDE_ERROR"
                            source_file as path
                
                Note: Validate configuration if schema provided
                If final_options.enable_validation and final_options.validation_schema is not None:
                    Let validation_result be validate_configuration_data with:
                        data as loaded_data
                        schema as final_options.validation_schema
                    
                    If not validation_result.valid:
                        If final_options.strict_mode:
                            Return LoadError with:
                                error_message as "Configuration validation failed: " plus validation_result.error_message
                                error_code as "VALIDATION_ERROR"
                                source_file as path
                        Otherwise:
                            Return LoadPartial with:
                                data as loaded_data
                                errors as validation_result.errors
                                source_file as path
                
                Note: Cache result if caching enabled
                If final_options.enable_caching:
                    cache_configuration_data with:
                        path as path
                        data as loaded_data
                        file_info as file_validation.file_info
                
                Return LoadSuccess with:
                    data as loaded_data
                    source_file as path
                    format as final_format
                    load_time as get_current_timestamp minus start_time
            
            When ParseError:
                Return LoadError with:
                    error_message as "Configuration parsing failed: " plus parse_result.error_message
                    error_code as "PARSE_ERROR"
                    source_file as path
    
    Catch error:
        Return LoadError with:
            error_message as "Configuration loading exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "LOADER_EXCEPTION"
            source_file as path

Process called "load_multiple_configuration_files" that takes file_paths as List[String] and merge_strategy as Optional[MergeStrategy] and options as Optional[LoaderOptions] returns LoadResult[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Let final_merge_strategy be merge_strategy if merge_strategy is not None else MERGE_DEEP
    Let final_options be options if options is not None else create_default_loader_options
    Let start_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Let merged_config be dictionary containing
    Let load_errors be list containing
    Let loaded_files be list containing
    
    Try:
        For each config_path in file_paths:
            Let load_result be load_configuration_file with:
                path as config_path
                format as None
                options as final_options
            
            Match load_result:
                When LoadSuccess:
                    Add config_path to loaded_files
                    Set merged_config to merge_configuration_data with:
                        base_config as merged_config
                        overlay_config as load_result.data
                        strategy as final_merge_strategy
                
                When LoadError:
                    If not final_options.allow_missing_files:
                        Return LoadError with:
                            error_message as "Failed to load required configuration file: " plus load_result.error_message
                            error_code as load_result.error_code
                            source_file as config_path
                    Otherwise:
                        Add load_result.error_message to load_errors
                
                When LoadPartial:
                    Add config_path to loaded_files
                    Set merged_config to merge_configuration_data with:
                        base_config as merged_config
                        overlay_config as load_result.data
                        strategy as final_merge_strategy
                    
                    For each error in load_result.errors:
                        Add error to load_errors
        
        If length of loaded_files is equal to 0:
            Return LoadError with:
                error_message as "No configuration files could be loaded"
                error_code as "NO_FILES_LOADED"
                source_file as join_list with list as file_paths and separator as ", "
        
        If length of load_errors is greater than 0:
            Return LoadPartial with:
                data as merged_config
                errors as load_errors
                source_file as join_list with list as loaded_files and separator as ", "
        
        Return LoadSuccess with:
            data as merged_config
            source_file as join_list with list as loaded_files and separator as ", "
            format as AUTO
            load_time as get_current_timestamp minus start_time
    
    Catch error:
        Return LoadError with:
            error_message as "Multiple configuration loading exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "MULTIPLE_LOADER_EXCEPTION"
            source_file as join_list with list as file_paths and separator as ", "

Process called "save_configuration_file" that takes data as Dictionary[String, Any] and path as String and format as Optional[ConfigFormat] and options as Optional[LoaderOptions] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_format be format if format is not None else detect_config_format with path as path
    Let final_options be options if options is not None else create_default_loader_options
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate file write access
        Let write_validation be validate_config_file_write_access with:
            path as path
            options as final_options
        
        If not write_validation.writable:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Cannot write to configuration file: " plus write_validation.error_message
                "error_code" as "FILE_WRITE_ACCESS_ERROR"
        
        Note: Serialize configuration data
        Let serialize_result be serialize_configuration_data with:
            data as data
            format as final_format
            options as final_options
        
        If not serialize_result.success:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Configuration serialization failed: " plus serialize_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "SERIALIZATION_ERROR"
        
        Note: Write to file
        Let write_result be write_config_file_content with:
            path as path
            content as serialize_result.content
            encoding as final_options.encoding
        
        If write_result.success:
            Note: Invalidate cache if enabled
            If final_options.enable_caching:
                invalidate_configuration_cache with path as path
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "path" as path
                "format" as final_format
                "bytes_written" as write_result.bytes_written
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Failed to write configuration file: " plus write_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "FILE_WRITE_ERROR"
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Configuration save exception: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "SAVE_EXCEPTION"
:End Note

Note: Configuration Format Detection and Parsing
Process called "detect_config_format" that takes path as String returns ConfigFormat:
    Let file_extension be get_file_extension with path as path
    Let lowercase_extension be lowercase of file_extension
    
    Match lowercase_extension:
        When ".json":
            Return JSON
        When ".yaml":
            Return YAML
        When ".yml":
            Return YAML
        When ".toml":
            Return TOML
        When ".ini":
            Return INI
        When ".xml":
            Return XML
        When ".env":
            Return ENV
        When ".properties":
            Return PROPERTIES
        Otherwise:
            Note: Try to detect from file content
            Let content_detection be detect_format_from_content with path as path
            If content_detection.detected:
                Return content_detection.format
            Otherwise:
                Return AUTO

Process called "parse_configuration_content" that takes content as String and format as ConfigFormat and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Match format:
            When JSON:
                Return parse_json_configuration with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            When YAML:
                Return parse_yaml_configuration with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            When TOML:
                Return parse_toml_configuration with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            When INI:
                Return parse_ini_configuration with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            When XML:
                Return parse_xml_configuration with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            When ENV:
                Return parse_env_configuration with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            When PROPERTIES:
                Return parse_properties_configuration with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            When AUTO:
                Return parse_auto_detect_configuration with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "type" as "ParseError"
                    "error_message" as "Unsupported configuration format: " plus format as String
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseError"
            "error_message" as "Configuration parsing exception: " plus error.message

Process called "serialize_configuration_data" that takes data as Dictionary[String, Any] and format as ConfigFormat and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Match format:
            When JSON:
                Return serialize_json_configuration with:
                    data as data
                    options as options
            
            When YAML:
                Return serialize_yaml_configuration with:
                    data as data
                    options as options
            
            When TOML:
                Return serialize_toml_configuration with:
                    data as data
                    options as options
            
            When INI:
                Return serialize_ini_configuration with:
                    data as data
                    options as options
            
            When XML:
                Return serialize_xml_configuration with:
                    data as data
                    options as options
            
            When ENV:
                Return serialize_env_configuration with:
                    data as data
                    options as options
            
            When PROPERTIES:
                Return serialize_properties_configuration with:
                    data as data
                    options as options
            
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "error_message" as "Unsupported configuration format for serialization: " plus format as String
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Configuration serialization exception: " plus error.message
:End Note

Note: Configuration Merging and Strategy Implementation
Process called "merge_configuration_data" that takes base_config as Dictionary[String, Any] and overlay_config as Dictionary[String, Any] and strategy as MergeStrategy returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Match strategy:
        When OVERRIDE:
            Return merge_with_override_strategy with:
                base as base_config
                overlay as overlay_config
        
        When MERGE_DEEP:
            Return merge_with_deep_strategy with:
                base as base_config
                overlay as overlay_config
        
        When MERGE_SHALLOW:
            Return merge_with_shallow_strategy with:
                base as base_config
                overlay as overlay_config
        
        When APPEND_LISTS:
            Return merge_with_append_lists_strategy with:
                base as base_config
                overlay as overlay_config
        
        When UNION_MAPS:
            Return merge_with_union_maps_strategy with:
                base as base_config
                overlay as overlay_config
        
        Otherwise:
            Return merge_with_deep_strategy with:
                base as base_config
                overlay as overlay_config

Process called "merge_with_deep_strategy" that takes base as Dictionary[String, Any] and overlay as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let result be deep_copy_dictionary with dict as base
    
    For each key, value in overlay:
        If result contains key:
            Let base_value be result[key]
            
            If is_dictionary with value as base_value and is_dictionary with value as value:
                Note: Recursively merge dictionaries
                Set result[key] to merge_with_deep_strategy with:
                    base as base_value
                    overlay as value
            Else If is_list with value as base_value and is_list with value as value:
                Note: Merge lists (replace by default, could be configured)
                Set result[key] to value
            Otherwise:
                Note: Override scalar values
                Set result[key] to value
        Otherwise:
            Note: Add new key
            Set result[key] to deep_copy_value with value as value
    
    Return result

Process called "merge_with_override_strategy" that takes base as Dictionary[String, Any] and overlay as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let result be deep_copy_dictionary with dict as base
    
    For each key, value in overlay:
        Set result[key] to deep_copy_value with value as value
    
    Return result

Process called "merge_with_shallow_strategy" that takes base as Dictionary[String, Any] and overlay as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let result be deep_copy_dictionary with dict as base
    
    For each key, value in overlay:
        If not result contains key:
            Set result[key] to deep_copy_value with value as value
    
    Return result

Process called "merge_with_append_lists_strategy" that takes base as Dictionary[String, Any] and overlay as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let result be deep_copy_dictionary with dict as base
    
    For each key, value in overlay:
        If result contains key:
            Let base_value be result[key]
            
            If is_list with value as base_value and is_list with value as value:
                Note: Append lists
                Let merged_list be deep_copy_list with list as base_value
                For each item in value:
                    Add deep_copy_value with value as item to merged_list
                Set result[key] to merged_list
            Otherwise:
                Set result[key] to deep_copy_value with value as value
        Otherwise:
            Set result[key] to deep_copy_value with value as value
    
    Return result

Process called "merge_with_union_maps_strategy" that takes base as Dictionary[String, Any] and overlay as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let result be deep_copy_dictionary with dict as base
    
    For each key, value in overlay:
        If result contains key:
            Let base_value be result[key]
            
            If is_dictionary with value as base_value and is_dictionary with value as value:
                Note: Union maps (keep both base and overlay values, overlay wins on conflicts)
                Set result[key] to merge_with_deep_strategy with:
                    base as base_value
                    overlay as value
            Otherwise:
                Set result[key] to deep_copy_value with value as value
        Otherwise:
            Set result[key] to deep_copy_value with value as value
    
    Return result
:End Note

Note: Configuration File Format Parsers
Process called "parse_json_configuration" that takes content as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Note: Remove comments if in strict mode (JSON doesn't support comments)
        Let processed_content be If options.strict_mode then content else remove_json_comments with content as content
        
        Let parsed_data be json.parse with content as processed_content
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseSuccess"
            "data" as parsed_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseError"
            "error_message" as "JSON parsing failed: " plus error.message

Process called "parse_yaml_configuration" that takes content as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let parsed_data be parse_yaml_content with:
            content as content
            safe_load as options.strict_mode
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseSuccess"
            "data" as parsed_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseError"
            "error_message" as "YAML parsing failed: " plus error.message

Process called "parse_toml_configuration" that takes content as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let parsed_data be parse_toml_content with content as content
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseSuccess"
            "data" as parsed_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseError"
            "error_message" as "TOML parsing failed: " plus error.message

Process called "parse_ini_configuration" that takes content as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let parsed_data be parse_ini_content with:
            content as content
            case_sensitive as true
            allow_no_value as not options.strict_mode
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseSuccess"
            "data" as parsed_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseError"
            "error_message" as "INI parsing failed: " plus error.message

Process called "parse_xml_configuration" that takes content as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let parsed_data be parse_xml_content with:
            content as content
            preserve_namespaces as true
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseSuccess"
            "data" as parsed_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseError"
            "error_message" as "XML parsing failed: " plus error.message

Process called "parse_env_configuration" that takes content as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let parsed_data be parse_env_content with:
            content as content
            expand_variables as options.enable_interpolation
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseSuccess"
            "data" as parsed_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseError"
            "error_message" as "ENV parsing failed: " plus error.message

Process called "parse_properties_configuration" that takes content as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let parsed_data be parse_properties_content with content as content
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseSuccess"
            "data" as parsed_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "type" as "ParseError"
            "error_message" as "Properties parsing failed: " plus error.message

Process called "parse_auto_detect_configuration" that takes content as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Try different formats in order of likelihood
    Let formats_to_try be list containing JSON, YAML, TOML, INI, ENV, PROPERTIES
    
    For each format in formats_to_try:
        Let parse_result be parse_configuration_content with:
            content as content
            format as format
            options as options
        
        If parse_result contains "type" and parse_result["type"] is equal to "ParseSuccess":
            Return parse_result
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "type" as "ParseError"
        "error_message" as "Could not auto-detect configuration format"
:End Note

Note: Configuration Interpolation and Preprocessing
Process called "interpolate_configuration_content" that takes content as String and syntax as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Match syntax:
            When "shell":
                Return interpolate_shell_syntax with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            When "mustache":
                Return interpolate_mustache_syntax with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            When "jinja":
                Return interpolate_jinja_syntax with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
            
            Otherwise:
                Return interpolate_shell_syntax with:
                    content as content
                    options as options
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Interpolation exception: " plus error.message

Process called "interpolate_shell_syntax" that takes content as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Note: Use environment module for shell-style variable expansion
        Let interpolated_content be environment.expand_environment_variables with:
            text as content
            allow_defaults as true
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "result" as interpolated_content
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Shell interpolation failed: " plus error.message

Process called "process_configuration_includes" that takes data as Dictionary[String, Any] and base_path as String and options as LoaderOptions and depth as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    If depth is greater than options.max_include_depth:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Maximum include depth exceeded: " plus depth as String
    
    Try:
        Let processed_data be deep_copy_dictionary with dict as data
        
        Note: Look for include directives
        If processed_data contains "include":
            Let include_value be processed_data["include"]
            
            If is_string with value as include_value:
                Note: Single include
                Let include_result be process_single_include with:
                    include_path as include_value
                    base_path as base_path
                    options as options
                    depth as depth plus 1
                
                If include_result.success:
                    Set processed_data to merge_configuration_data with:
                        base_config as include_result.data
                        overlay_config as processed_data
                        strategy as MERGE_DEEP
                
                Note: Remove include directive
                Remove "include" from processed_data
            
            Else If is_list with value as include_value:
                Note: Multiple includes
                Let merged_includes be dictionary containing
                
                For each include_path in include_value:
                    Let include_result be process_single_include with:
                        include_path as include_path
                        base_path as base_path
                        options as options
                        depth as depth plus 1
                    
                    If include_result.success:
                        Set merged_includes to merge_configuration_data with:
                            base_config as merged_includes
                            overlay_config as include_result.data
                            strategy as MERGE_DEEP
                
                Set processed_data to merge_configuration_data with:
                    base_config as merged_includes
                    overlay_config as processed_data
                    strategy as MERGE_DEEP
                
                Note: Remove include directive
                Remove "include" from processed_data
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "merged_data" as processed_data
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Include processing failed: " plus error.message

Process called "process_single_include" that takes include_path as String and base_path as String and options as LoaderOptions and depth as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let full_path be resolve_include_path with:
        include_path as include_path
        base_path as base_path
    
    Let load_result be load_configuration_file with:
        path as full_path
        format as None
        options as options
    
    Match load_result:
        When LoadSuccess:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "data" as load_result.data
        
        When LoadError:
            If options.allow_missing_files:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as true
                    "data" as dictionary containing
            Otherwise:
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "success" as false
                    "error_message" as load_result.error_message
        
        When LoadPartial:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "data" as load_result.data
:End Note

Note: Configuration Caching System
Process called "check_configuration_cache" that takes path as String and file_info as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let cache be get_global_config_cache
    
    If cache.cached_configs contains path:
        Let cached_timestamp be cache.cache_timestamps[path]
        Let cached_hash be cache.cache_hashes[path]
        Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
        
        Note: Check if cache is expired
        If current_time minus cached_timestamp is less than cache.ttl_seconds:
            Note: Check if file has been modified
            Let current_hash be calculate_file_hash with file_info as file_info
            
            If current_hash is equal to cached_hash:
                Set cache.cache_hits to cache.cache_hits plus 1
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "found" as true
                    "expired" as false
                    "data" as cache.cached_configs[path]
    
    Set cache.cache_misses to cache.cache_misses plus 1
    Return dictionary containing:
        "found" as false
        "expired" as true
        "data" as dictionary containing

Process called "cache_configuration_data" that takes path as String and data as Dictionary[String, Any] and file_info as Dictionary[String, Any] returns None:
    Let cache be get_global_config_cache
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    
    Note: Implement LRU eviction if cache is full
    If length of cache.cached_configs is greater than or equal to cache.max_cache_size:
        evict_oldest_cache_entry with cache as cache
    
    Set cache.cached_configs[path] to deep_copy_dictionary with dict as data
    Set cache.cache_timestamps[path] to current_time
    Set cache.cache_hashes[path] to calculate_file_hash with file_info as file_info
    
    Return None

Process called "invalidate_configuration_cache" that takes path as String returns None:
    Let cache be get_global_config_cache
    
    If cache.cached_configs contains path:
        Remove path from cache.cached_configs
        Remove path from cache.cache_timestamps
        Remove path from cache.cache_hashes
    
    Return None

Process called "clear_configuration_cache" returns None:
    Let cache be get_global_config_cache
    
    Set cache.cached_configs to dictionary containing
    Set cache.cache_timestamps to dictionary containing
    Set cache.cache_hashes to dictionary containing
    Set cache.cache_hits to 0
    Set cache.cache_misses to 0
    
    Return None
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "create_default_loader_options" returns LoaderOptions:
    Return LoaderOptions with:
        strict_mode as false
        allow_missing_files as true
        enable_interpolation as true
        interpolation_syntax as "shell"
        enable_includes as false
        max_include_depth as 10
        enable_caching as true
        cache_ttl as 300.0
        enable_validation as false
        validation_schema as None
        encoding as "utf-8"
        file_size_limit as 10485760
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "validate_config_file_access" that takes path as String and options as LoaderOptions returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let file_exists be file.exists with path as path
        If not file_exists:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "accessible" as false
                "error_message" as "Configuration file does not exist: " plus path
                "file_info" as dictionary containing
        
        Let file_readable be file.is_readable with path as path
        If not file_readable:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "accessible" as false
                "error_message" as "Configuration file is not readable: " plus path
                "file_info" as dictionary containing
        
        Let file_size be file.get_size with path as path
        If file_size is greater than options.file_size_limit:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "accessible" as false
                "error_message" as "Configuration file too large: " plus file_size as String plus " bytes (limit: " plus options.file_size_limit as String plus ")"
                "file_info" as dictionary containing
        
        Let file_info be dictionary containing:
            "path" as path
            "size" as file_size
            "last_modified" as file.get_last_modified with path as path
            "readable" as true
            "exists" as true
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "accessible" as true
            "error_message" as ""
            "file_info" as file_info
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "accessible" as false
            "error_message" as "File access validation failed: " plus error.message
            "file_info" as dictionary containing

Process called "get_file_extension" that takes path as String returns String:
    Let last_dot_index be last_index_of with text as path and substring as "."
    If last_dot_index is equal to -1:
        Return ""
    Otherwise:
        Return substring of path from last_dot_index to length of path

Process called "get_directory_from_path" that takes path as String returns String:
    Let last_slash_index be last_index_of with text as path and substring as "/"
    If last_slash_index is equal to -1:
        Return "."
    Otherwise:
        Return substring of path from 0 to last_slash_index

Process called "resolve_include_path" that takes include_path as String and base_path as String returns String:
    If starts_with with text as include_path and prefix as "/":
        Note: Absolute path
        Return include_path
    Otherwise:
        Note: Relative path
        Return base_path plus "/" plus include_path

Process called "deep_copy_dictionary" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let result be dictionary containing
    For each key, value in dict:
        Set result[key] to deep_copy_value with value as value
    Return result

Process called "deep_copy_value" that takes value as Any returns Any:
    If is_dictionary with value as value:
        Return deep_copy_dictionary with dict as value
    Else If is_list with value as value:
        Return deep_copy_list with list as value
    Otherwise:
        Return value

Process called "deep_copy_list" that takes list as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let result be list containing
    For each item in list:
        Add deep_copy_value with value as item to result
    Return result

Process called "is_dictionary" that takes value as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Implementation should check if value is a dictionary
    Return false

Process called "is_list" that takes value as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Implementation should check if value is a list
    Return false

Process called "is_string" that takes value as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Implementation should check if value is a string
    Return false

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Returns current system timestamp with microsecond precision
    Let time_result be system_call_current_time
    Return time_result.seconds as Float plus (time_result.microseconds as Float divided by 1000000.0)

Process called "lowercase" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Implementation should convert string to lowercase
    Return text

Process called "join_list" that takes list as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Let result be ""
    Let first be true
    For each item in list:
        If not first:
            Set result to result plus separator
        Set result to result plus item
        Set first to false
    Return result

Process called "last_index_of" that takes text as String and substring as String returns Integer:
    Note: Implementation should return last index of substring in text
    Return -1

Process called "substring" that takes text as String and start as Integer and end as Integer returns String:
    Note: Implementation should extract substring
    Return text

Process called "starts_with" that takes text as String and prefix as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Implementation should check if text starts with prefix
    Return false
:End Note

