Process called "parse_env_content" that takes content as String and expand_variables as Boolean returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Parse .env file content
    Let result be dictionary containing
    Let lines be split_string with value as content and separator as "\n"
    
    For each line in lines:
        Let trimmed_line be trim_whitespace with value as line
        
        Note: Skip empty lines and comments
        If trimmed_line is equal to "" or starts_with with text as trimmed_line and prefix as "Note:":
            Continue
        
        Note: Find key=value pairs
        Let equals_index be index_of with text as trimmed_line and substring as "="
        If equals_index is not equal to -1:
            Let key be trim_whitespace with value as substring of trimmed_line from 0 to equals_index
            Let value be trim_whitespace with value as substring of trimmed_line from (equals_index plus 1) to length of trimmed_line
            
            Note: Remove quotes if present
            If starts_with with text as value and prefix as "\"" and ends_with with text as value and suffix as "\"":
                Set value to substring of value from 1 to (length of value minus 1)
            
            Set result[key] to value
    
    Return result

